sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Admin / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as LlamaStack Operator<br/>(redhat-ods-applications)
    participant Pod as LlamaStack Server Pod<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant Ingress as Ingress Controller<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant Client as External Client

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Admin,Pod: Flow 1: LlamaStackDistribution Reconciliation
        Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply LlamaStackDistribution CR
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (HTTPS/443, SA Bearer Token)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Read CR spec (HTTPS/443, SA Bearer Token)
        Operator->>Operator: Render manifests via Kustomize<br/>Apply transformer plugins

        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Deployment (HTTPS/443)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Service (HTTPS/443)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ServiceAccount (HTTPS/443)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update RoleBinding → anyuid SCC (HTTPS/443)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update NetworkPolicy (HTTPS/443)

        alt spec.network.exposeRoute=true
            Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Ingress (HTTPS/443)
        end
        alt spec.storage configured
            Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PVC (HTTPS/443)
        end
        alt spec.autoscaling configured
            Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update HPA (HTTPS/443)
            Operator->>K8sAPI: Remove spec.replicas from Deployment
        end
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update PDB (HTTPS/443)

        Note over Operator,Pod: Wait for Deployment ready
        Operator->>Pod: GET /v1/health (HTTP/8321, plaintext)
        Pod-->>Operator: 200 OK
        Operator->>Pod: GET /v1/providers (HTTP/8321, plaintext)
        Pod-->>Operator: Provider info JSON
        Operator->>Pod: GET /v1/version (HTTP/8321, plaintext)
        Pod-->>Operator: Version info JSON
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Update CR status (HTTPS/443, SA Bearer Token)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 2: CA Bundle Aggregation
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Read user CA ConfigMap<br/>(direct client, HTTPS/443)
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: ConfigMap data
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Read odh-trusted-ca-bundle<br/>(direct client, HTTPS/443)
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: ConfigMap data (may not exist)
        Operator->>Operator: Parse PEM blocks<br/>Validate X.509 certs<br/>Reject non-CERTIFICATE types<br/>Enforce size limits (10MB, 1000 certs)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update managed CA ConfigMap<br/>(HTTPS/443)
        Note over Pod: Pod mounts managed CA ConfigMap<br/>via SSL_CERT_FILE env var
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Client,Pod: Flow 3: External Access (when exposeRoute=true)
        Client->>Ingress: HTTP request (80/TCP)
        Ingress->>Pod: Forward to {instance}-service<br/>(8321/TCP, HTTP, plaintext)
        Pod-->>Ingress: Response
        Ingress-->>Client: Response
    end
